<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1436,1028,1236]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1028,1055]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Palps not more than 4 times longer than wide. Antero-lateral setae numerous (30â€“86 pairs). Setae 
<emphasis box="[1388,1436,1029,1055]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">dm1</emphasis>
filiform. Setae 
<emphasis box="[321,369,1065,1091]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">dm3</emphasis>
absent. All peripheral setae apically expanded and arranged in 1 row. One pair of genital setae 
<emphasis box="[151,179,1101,1127]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">g1</emphasis>
present. Pseudanal series represented by 1 or 5 pairs of paddle-shaped setae 
<emphasis box="[1039,1064,1102,1127]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">ps</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1436,1028,1236]" box="[199,1237,1136,1164]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
